#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/117425/ Hero id 117425 | Guide id
#: 696
msgid "This hero power is mainly used to gain 1 gold per turn, similar to Murloc Holmes."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/118510/ Hero id 118510 | Guide id
#: 698
msgid "Mothership is the best one to pick. Finish the hero power as soon as possible by buying everything that costs effectively 1 ([[Sellemental||64038]], [[Enchanted Lasso||104502]]). Make sure you buy summon units ([[Manasaber||98831]]) to farm 2+ protoss minions per turn. Do not spend any gold leveling to 3 until you've unlocked your minion."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/117409/ Hero id 117409 | Guide id
#: 695
msgid "Use this hero power like reno and use it on the first value generator you see, such as [[Bigwig Bandit||122179]]. If you don't find an early value generator, then use it on a core card for your direction."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/116926/ Hero id 116926 | Guide id
#: 694
msgid "You want to copy the same, strong spell over and over. With an early [[Strike Oil||104029]] or [[Chef's Choice||105664]], you can hero power every single turn to start printing Strike Oils. Then, later on you generate a strong spell such as [[Temperature Shift||117670]] every turn."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/118509/ Hero id 118509 | Guide id
#: 697
msgid "The battlecruiser upgrades are very strong, but only starting from tavern 4. Don't invest too much into the upgrades early, only if it makes sense goldwise, and then start playing into your buddy."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/116920/ Hero id 116920 | Guide id
#: 700
msgid "Always hero power the first 3 turns, freezing a 2 cost spell turn 1 if you can. Turn 4 onwards, you can choose to stop hero powering if buying a good minion is better. Definitely stop hero powering after turn 6 if you don't want to die."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/120358/ Hero id 120358 | Guide id
#: 699
msgid "The Zerg provides guaranteed tempo. Level up your Zerg to tavern 3 on turn 5 or 6, and you must stay on tavern 2 to do so. Then, fully play into Infestor by cycling cards that give multiple cards such as [[Enchanted Lasso||104502]] and [[Patient Scout||97604]]."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/122925/ Hero id 122925 | Guide id
#: 702
msgid "Summon cards such as [[Manasaber||98831]] or [[Icky Imp||74910]] are great because they'll give you more attacks so you can finish the hero power ASAP."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/120649/ Hero id 120649 | Guide id
#: 701
msgid "Getting a value quest such as Pagle's Fishing Rod or Guiding Candle on Turn 8 is usually pretty sick, depending on your setup."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/96870/ Hero id 96870 | Guide id
#: 381
msgid "This hero provides some early game tempo, and has some lategame potential with venomous on random cards."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/82110/ Hero id 82110 | Guide id
#: 213
msgid "Must have beasts, undeads, and/or demons to start farming hero power early on. [[Manasaber||98831]] and [[Icky Imp||74910]] are premium on this hero."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/99033/ Hero id 99033 | Guide id
#: 425
msgid "Hero power and buddy has extra synergy with [[Drakkari Enchanter||101314]], allowing you to copy more copies of powerful cards."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/86013/ Hero id 86013 | Guide id
#: 272
msgid "Your hero power will save some HP, but don't play into it."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/89293/ Hero id 89293 | Guide id
#: 345
msgid "Strong hero power used to fill out your board in the early game, and duplicate key cards for your board in the mid-late game."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/61910/ Hero id 61910 | Guide id
#: 86
msgid "The more summons your board has, the more attacks will happen. Value cards that summon such as [[Manasaber||98831]] or [[Icky Imp||74910]] in the earlygame."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/84867/ Hero id 84867 | Guide id
#: 322
msgid "After turn 1, keep track of everyone's tavern 1 unit! Murloc Holmes might have you choose between tier 1 units in the first few turns."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/101345/ Hero id 101345 | Guide id
#: 424
msgid "Hero power on turn 3, 4, and 5. Value generating buddies are the best."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/101130/ Hero id 101130 | Guide id
#: 452
msgid "Buy most pirates in the early game to fill out your board fast so you can level."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/98726/ Hero id 98726 | Guide id
#: 420
msgid "This hero is best used in Beast comps to target the [[Goldrinn, the Great Wolf||59955]] or Undead comps to target a reborn deathrattle undead ([[Friendly Geist||120219]])."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/68129/ Hero id 68129 | Guide id
#: 35
msgid "This hero is the best with cycle tribes, because the hero power benefits from you buying a ton of cards. These tribes include Pirates, Elementals, and Murlocs, and try to play one of these compositions."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/86291/ Hero id 86291 | Guide id
#: 308
msgid "Most games your curve will be leveling to tavern 3 on turn 4, and then hero powering either your turn 5 shop or leveling. If you level on turn 5, then hero power your best tier 4 shop."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/97186/ Hero id 97186 | Guide id
#: 371
msgid "Use your hero power on [[Cadaver Caretaker||113158]] for free triples!"
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/103500/ Hero id 103500 | Guide id
#: 453
msgid "Build your gameplan around your buddy."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57924/ Hero id 57924 | Guide id
#: 25
msgid "Mainly a tempo hero that gives you free stats throughout the midgame. Don't play too hard into it."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/97813/ Hero id 97813 | Guide id
#: 402
msgid "Do not hero power on tavern 2 because tavern 2 creations are terrible. Instead, hero power on tavern 3+. Coin + reborn creation is the strongest on tavern 3 or 4, and tavern 4+ unlocks venomous and poisonous undeads that you can reborn."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/103477/ Hero id 103477 | Guide id
#: 504
msgid "[[Moira Bronzebeard||103502]] and [[King Varian||102998]] are generally the best 7 drops to pick because they're flexible. Naga's and Demon's 7 drop are pretty good too. Beast's 7 drop is only good with a [[Manasaber||98831]] turn 1."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/79719/ Hero id 79719 | Guide id
#: 166
msgid "Brukan's most common hero power is Lightning invocation, which is great to pop Divine Shields on your opponent's board."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/58027/ Hero id 58027 | Guide id
#: 114
msgid "Try to lean into a [[Brann Bronzebeard||96786]] comp with this hero, such as Elemental or Murlocs, so you can keep a [[Tavern Tempest||64077]] or [[Magicfin's Apprentice]] on your board and proc it every turn."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/92960/ Hero id 92960 | Guide id
#: 324
msgid "Most of the time, the quest that you can complete the fastest and easiest is the best choice. For example, a summon quest with a [[Manasaber||98831]] opener is premium, but without any summons it's pretty bad."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60211/ Hero id 60211 | Guide id
#: 122
msgid "The less armor a hero starts off with, the better pick it'll be with Finley. Snake Eyes starts with 6 armor, but if you pick it with Finley then you gain some extra armor with a good hero power."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/74646/ Hero id 74646 | Guide id
#: 150
msgid "MUST Have [[All-Seeing Elder||122104]] on this hero. It will get your hero power proc, which you can then trigger with [[Monstrous Macaw||62230]] or [[Hawkstrider]] Herald."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57944/ Hero id 57944 | Guide id
#: 27
msgid "Value generator 4 drops are by far the best ones, such as [[Bigwig Bandit||122179]] or [[Campfire Shadow||122481]]. Same thing with value generating 3 drops, such as [[Lost City Looter||122175]]."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60214/ Hero id 60214 | Guide id
#: 125
msgid "Typically, Murlocs and Elementals can utilize Brann the best, so you must have those tribes in."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60369/ Hero id 60369 | Guide id
#: 38
msgid "Only pick with Mechs in. Divine Shielded units such as [[Cord Puller||110101]] are premium in the early game. If you find no Divine Shields, then value units with higher HP."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/105314/ Hero id 105314 | Guide id
#: 658
msgid "If you roll a 3+ turn 1, level turn 1. If you roll a 1 on turn 1, do NOT hero power on turn 2. Other than that, hero power whenever it's available."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/61488/ Hero id 61488 | Guide id
#: 39
msgid "You must level to 4 on turn 5 on this hero! Either level to tavern 3 on turn 3 or turn 4 and then level to 4 on turn 5. Start hero powering every turn starting from turn 5. Even though you may start the game at low HP, you have to start getting your dragons up early on."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/105434/ Hero id 105434 | Guide id
#: 604
msgid "You don't have to hero power every turn, only when you have 1 gold left over. For example, turn 2 you should still just level and not hero power."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/105431/ Hero id 105431 | Guide id
#: 600
msgid "Don't expect much value from this hero power, it's basically Patchwerk 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60370/ Hero id 60370 | Guide id
#: 54
msgid "Force Dragons on this hero, using [[Prized Promo-Drake||72073]] and [[Twilight Watcher||122442]] plus [[Persistent Poet||108463]] to stabilize."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/75702/ Hero id 75702 | Guide id
#: 16
msgid "I recommend starting with a 1-3 flightpath to line up the discovers with your buddy."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/79618/ Hero id 79618 | Guide id
#: 252
msgid "It's worth buying the highest attack units in your shop and pointy arrows to complete your quest ASAP. You ideally want this quest done turn 6 the latest. Then, start leveling and force a Naga comp."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/85125/ Hero id 85125 | Guide id
#: 293
msgid "This hero provides free early game tempo. Overall decent."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/64403/ Hero id 64403 | Guide id 5
msgid "Rally units are really nice with this hero power to attack twice with them."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/64480/ Hero id 64480 | Guide id
#: 11
msgid "A ticket is roughly worth 1 gold, so any 1 cost spell with a ticket is worth buying. However, don't buy useless units for the sake of buying a ticket."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60362/ Hero id 60362 | Guide id
#: 127
msgid "Try to hero power turns 2-4 if you can. You can usually achieve this most efficiently by leveling to tavern 2 on turn 3. After that, hero power whenever you have 1 gold left, and don't feel like you have to press it."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/113310/ Hero id 113310 | Guide id
#: 683
msgid "Don't be sad to choose Neutral lesser trinkets such as Well Oiled Can, they're all generally decent."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/62242/ Hero id 62242 | Guide id
#: 48
msgid "With Eudora, hero power every single turn starting from turn 1. This is done by leveling to tavern 2 on turn 3 and leveling to tavern 3 on turn 4. Your first hero power reward should be completed on tavern 3, turn 4. Use your second hero power reward on turn 8, and then stop hero powering from turn 9 onwards."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/62268/ Hero id 62268 | Guide id
#: 50
msgid "Most commonly, you use your hero power on turn 6 when you level to 4 in order to stabilize on tavern 4. Stabilize means you buy either good standalone cards or good synergy with your board."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/63604/ Hero id 63604 | Guide id 3
msgid "Always think about your next turn! On turn 1, freeze a 2 cost spell or buy a [[Southsea Busker||98501]] so your turn 2 is much cleaner. Omu almost always levels to tavern 3 on turn 4 while buying a minion."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60213/ Hero id 60213 | Guide id
#: 124
msgid "Hero power when it works out goldwise. For example, on turn 4 you may level to tavern 3 and hero power for 1. When your hero power costs 5, stop hero powering."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57634/ Hero id 57634 | Guide id
#: 109
msgid "Illidan is great with Rally cards because attacking first with them is quite important. It also allows for you to proc important rallys twice."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/58535/ Hero id 58535 | Guide id
#: 12
msgid "Patchwerk 2.0, only press this hero power if you don't have a better way to spend 1 gold on maybe on turns 3, 4, or 5. The hero power is decent with Drakkari Enchanter because it upgrades twice and procs twice."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/62266/ Hero id 62266 | Guide id
#: 49
msgid "ONLY PICKABLE WITH BEASTS! Hero power 1 drops the first few turns and try to discover [[Southsea Busker||98501]], [[Ominous Seer||117553]], or [[Alleycat||96758]]. Then, you can hero power the battlecry minion again and try to discover more battlecries."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/59806/ Hero id 59806 | Guide id
#: 118
msgid "Use your hero power for early game tempo, saving HP and allowing you to level aggressively."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/61914/ Hero id 61914 | Guide id
#: 47
msgid "Early game, your hero power is used to buy minions for 1 gold. Late game, you can hero power 5 drop and 6 drop spells in your shop to \"buy\" them for cheap."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/80239/ Hero id 80239 | Guide id
#: 167
msgid "Try to play a comp that concentrates stats if you can. Examples include T4 Quilboars or [[Insatiable Ur'zul||72060]]."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/73940/ Hero id 73940 | Guide id
#: 87
msgid "Buff some divine shields and play for top 4. This hero doesn't have enough economy to consistently win."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/80832/ Hero id 80832 | Guide id
#: 232
msgid "Even though you want to play Mechs eventually, Undead and Beasts provide the best early game summons so you can start having minions die early on."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/61490/ Hero id 61490 | Guide id
#: 41
msgid "BEST PLAYED WITH BEASTS! Early game, after you play a Battlecry unit such as [[Alleycat||96758]] or [[Southsea Busker||98501]], hero power it to reroll it into something better. Lategame, you can use your hero power to reroll your 6 drops if you don't like them."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57635/ Hero id 57635 | Guide id
#: 110
msgid "Early game, hero power and freeze every turn, including turn 1, until you hit something you like from a higher tier. Value generating cards are the best, such as [[Lost City Looter||122175]] on 3, [[Bigwig Bandit||122179]] or [[Campfire Shadow||122481]] on 4, and [[Holo Rover||115674]] on 6"
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/76521/ Hero id 76521 | Guide id
#: 143
msgid "You have the option to reborn the buddy with [[Prosthetic Hand||112364]] and summon scam such as [[Deadly Spore||65031]] or [[Leeroy, the Reckless||90425]]. This hero isn't that good though."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/63601/ Hero id 63601 | Guide id 1
msgid "If you find an [[Alleycat||96758]] turn 1, swap it every turn (except turn 2 because it should be frozen in your shop), taking a 3 drop with your tabbycat triple turn 3 and taking a 5 drop on turn 6."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/59814/ Hero id 59814 | Guide id
#: 120
msgid "Use your bananas early game on a good unit to save HP in the earlygame and then play normally from there. If you don't find a good unit on turn 1, you should use all of them turn 3 the latest."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/58534/ Hero id 58534 | Guide id
#: 30
msgid "The most common curve with this hero is to level hero power on turn 4, so turn 5 you can buy 2 good 4 drops, and play the game from there."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/59831/ Hero id 59831 | Guide id
#: 121
msgid "Hero power on turns 1, 3, 4, and 5, and possibly 6 to fill out your board. On turn 2 you should level. After that, forget about the hero power."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57893/ Hero id 57893 | Guide id
#: 111
msgid "Hero power the first 6 turns (except turn 2), and be tavern 4 by turn 6. Then, you don't have to hero power every turn, only when the tribe is useful to you."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/64475/ Hero id 64475 | Guide id 6
msgid "Try not to spend a lot of money leveling on this hero. You can buy elementals, and then level to taverns 4, 5 or 6 when it's 3 or less gold."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/61912/ Hero id 61912 | Guide id
#: 45
msgid "This hero power isn't strong enough to play into, so just play normally and enjoy occasional free gold."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60366/ Hero id 60366 | Guide id
#: 129
msgid "You MUST play a cycle comp on this hero such as APM Pirates or Elementals - NOT Undeads, Beast, or Mechs!"
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/66196/ Hero id 66196 | Guide id
#: 13
msgid "Hero power until turn 6 (except when you level on turn 2), and generally stop hero powering after that."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/58435/ Hero id 58435 | Guide id
#: 29
msgid "This hero benefits from cycle tribes being in, which are Elementals Murlocs and Pirates. Then, cycle every free card ([[Sellemental||64038]], [[Patient Scout||97604]], [[Tavern Tempest||64077]]) and find an APM direction to start scaling."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57892/ Hero id 57892 | Guide id
#: 24
msgid "Buy every single cheap card that costs 1 ([[Pointy Arrow||100596]], [[Patient Scout||97604]]) the first 6 turns. Stay on tavern 2 on turn 6 to finish the hero power. Then, if you can, double level turn 7 to not be underleveled."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/58021/ Hero id 58021 | Guide id
#: 112
msgid "If you have a deathrattle you really want to copy, then taunt it and choose Pack Tactics. Otherwise, usually choose Venomstrike Trap."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/64400/ Hero id 64400 | Guide id 4
msgid "Mediocre hero power in the early game, enables spell synergy mid-late game such as [[Shadowdancer||120662]] or Bounty Pirates."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57633/ Hero id 57633 | Guide id
#: 108
msgid "The hero power isn't that good, so only use it when you have one gold left over and don't play into too much."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/67356/ Hero id 67356 | Guide id
#: 17
msgid "The best tier 1 spells are discover tier 1, 2 coins or 3 refreshes. The best tier 2 spells are generally Great Deal and On the House."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/59805/ Hero id 59805 | Guide id
#: 117
msgid "Generically powerful hero!"
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/70838/ Hero id 70838 | Guide id
#: 210
msgid "Patchwerk 2.0, play the game normally and your hero will passively preserve some HP. Your main goal on this hero is to naturally find a direction, your hero doesn't help with it."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57891/ Hero id 57891 | Guide id
#: 23
msgid "In the early game, buy every [[Tad||87060]] and [[Patient Scout||97604]] as they generate you money. In the lategame, Gallywix relies on [[Brann Bronzebeard||96786]] to cycle lots of cards to ramp up economy. You must play a cycle composition with this hero, so try not to go Beasts or Undeads. If Elementals are in, the best strategy is to stay on tavern 2 and buy every + gold card (such as Tad or Scout) and every baller. You want to scale Divine Shield units only plus your buddy."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/71463/ Hero id 71463 | Guide id
#: 22
msgid "If you plan on eating the entire shop, swap your largest attack unit into the shop first so you can turn your hero power attack into permanent attack. [[Channel the Devourer||100899]] and [[Mounting Avalanche||122862]] are other ways to turn temporary stats from your hero power into permanant stats."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57929/ Hero id 57929 | Guide id
#: 26
msgid "Hero power in the early/mid game if you have 1 gold leftover (such as turn 3). Your hero power is very useful in the lategame, but you want to focus on building a good comp first. Going Divine Shield + Venom with Murlocs in is a viable backup strategy."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/81569/ Hero id 81569 | Guide id
#: 222
msgid "Very often the curve on this hero is to level to tavern 3 on turn 4 and level to 4 on turn 5 so you can unlock your 4 drop as soon as possible. The best 4 drops to pick are the ones that generate value every turn such as [[Bigwig Bandit||122179]]."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/77516/ Hero id 77516 | Guide id
#: 142
msgid "Usually go 3 on 3 on this hero. In your first 3 turns, try to hero power the same tribe to maximize your chances of getting a higher tavern tier card. If you hero power all different tribes, you have the possibility of only discovering 1 drops from your hero power."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60372/ Hero id 60372 | Guide id
#: 42
msgid "Flurgl is best in an economy-centric lobby, because the hero power benefits from cycling cards. Even though you're a Murloc hero, pirate or elemental cycle comps utilizing [[Brann Bronzebeard||96786]] can make a ton of use out of your hero power."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/63319/ Hero id 63319 | Guide id
#: 52
msgid "You have a lot of armor to work with, so don't be scared of leveling fast. You're basically Patchwerk with less HP, but higher chance to win the lobby."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/60367/ Hero id 60367 | Guide id
#: 10
msgid "You can afford to stabilize on lower tiers and save HP so when you steal directional cards from your opponent you are healthy enough to play into them."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/59203/ Hero id 59203 | Guide id
#: 33
msgid "Reborn the amalgam using [[Prosthetic Hand||112364]] or [[Sprightly Scarab||108909]]. Shield the Amalgam using [[Hogwatcher||122737]] or [[Annoy-o-Module||96812]]. Resummon the Amalgam using [[Cultist S'thara||106501]]"
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/66483/ Hero id 66483 | Guide id
#: 14
msgid "Beasts and Undead compositions are the best for fish."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/58044/ Hero id 58044 | Guide id
#: 115
msgid "Definitely hero power + buy spell on turn 1 if you can, level on turn 2, and hero power + buy on turn 3. You don't have to hero power after that unless you really need the gold."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57947/ Hero id 57947 | Guide id
#: 44
msgid "Buy every pirate in the early game. Hero powering is also usually better than buying a non-pirate card."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/57946/ Hero id 57946 | Guide id
#: 28
msgid "Infinite access to divine shields and reborns for your mechs. If you don't need those, pick [[Accord-o-Tron||98576]] for gold or [[Whirring Protector||122743]] for strength."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/74631/ Hero id 74631 | Guide id
#: 37
msgid "Economy cards such as [[Freedealing Gambler||61049]], [[Sellemental||64038]], and [[Patient Scout||97604]] are must buys to get hero power procs early on."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/59807/ Hero id 59807 | Guide id
#: 119
msgid "Prioritize first buffing the shop and then finding [[Insatiable Ur'zul||72060]] to best capitalize on the 2 demons per turn."
msgstr ""

#: https://hsreplay.net/battlegrounds/heroes/61489/ Hero id 61489 | Guide id
#: 40
msgid "Turn 1 if you have a 2 cost spell in your first shop, buy it and then roll and you'll likely roll into a 1 cost spell that you can then buy. Same thing with coin, buy it and roll and hope to get a 2 cost spell in your next shop."
msgstr ""

